y_ids":[""]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"upper arm, bracchium, humerus","examples":[{"text":"فِي ذِرَاعِ ٱلْإِنْسَانِ ثَلَاثَةُ عِظَامٍ: اِثْنَتَانِ فِي ٱلسَّاعِدِ ٱسْمَاهُمَا ٱلزَّنْدُ وَٱلْكُعْبُرَةُ وَوَاحِدَةٌ فِي ٱلْعَضُدِ.","english":"There are three bones in the human arm: two in the lower arm (called the ulna and the radius) and one in the upper arm."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"something or someone that gives man strength, assistant etc.","tags":["figuratively"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"side, lateral, brink, border, region, quarter, area, tract, boundary","tags":["obsolete"],"examples":[{"text":"لوجع الْأَسْنَان وضع ورق الكبيكج على عضد العليل من جَانب سنه العليل سكن الوجع من سَاعَة وَإِن أحدث فِي العصب قرحَة فَيَنْبَغِي أَن يعالج بعد ذَلِك.","english":"For tooth-ache put leaves of spearwort onto the ill spot from the side of the aching tooth and it will attain relief from the ache within an hour and if a sore spawn in the tissue then it should be treated after that."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be strong for, to succor, to support, to aid"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to reinforce, to corroborate, to strengthen, to be strong for, to sustain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَضَدَ (ʕaḍada) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"what is lopped from trees, cuttings"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null}